I am truly obliged to you for your interesting and welcome letter, and its accompanying invitation.<note>Untraced; presumably linked to Robinson’s move to Chigwell, setting of the Maypole Inn in <hi rend="italic">Barnaby Rudge</hi>.</note> But I regret that I cannot accept the latter; as I shall, on the day to which it refers, be parting from my youngest son,<note>Edward Bulwer Lytton Dickens (“Plorn”), (1852-1902).</note> bound for Australia and Bush Life.<note>Edward left London, 26 Sep, on his way to Australia, where he was to join his brother, Alfred, having completed his course at the Agricultural College, Cirencester in July.</note>
